en begins on Monday in relative obscurity, but could end the week as one of the stars of these Games - and not solely from a British perspective.\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmarthen\", \"score\": 0.9999639432519404, \"rank\": 3.6040476384580296e-05, \"text\": \"Carmarthen\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmarthen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmarthen\"}, {\"begin\": 434, \"end\": 441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8325799076810546, \"rank\": 0.19565002311157528, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 328}, {\"ngram\": \"relative obscurity\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 350}, {\"ngram\": \"the stars\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quietly, understatedly, she has become the powerhouse of global cycle sprinting and is aiming to emulate Britain's cycling knights Sir Chris Hoy and Sir Jason Kenny, both of whom will be present at the Sain-Quentin-en-Yvelines velodrome this week, in winning triple sprint gold at a single Games.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9977096628406946, \"rank\": 0.0022955565998459887, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the powerhouse\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 509}, {\"ngram\": \"global cycle sprinting\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 535}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sain-Quentin-en-Yvelines velodrome\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"triple sprint gold\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 733}, {\"ngram\": \"a single Games\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chance one for the new golden girl of the track comes in the team sprint tonight, with her predecessor as golden girl, Dame Laura Kenny, saying: \\\"I am picking Emma Finucane to become a triple Olympic champion in the women's team sprint, the individual sprint and the keirin.\\\"\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999907492861403, \"rank\": 9.245628366532346e-06, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chance\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 760}, {\"ngram\": \"the new golden girl\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"the team sprint\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"her predecessor\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 856}, {\"ngram\": \"golden girl\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 871}, {\"ngram\": \"a triple Olympic champion\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's team sprint\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual sprint\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"the keirin\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenny has GB winning as many as eight golds on the track in the coming days, which would surpass the record seven achieved at London 2012 and the six at the subsequent two Olympics.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999979459062, \"rank\": 2.053982501037843e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kenny\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"GB\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1043}, {\"ngram\": \"as many as eight golds\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"the coming days\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"the record\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"the subsequent two Olympics\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hoy believes that five golds are a more realistic target and that \\\"the women sprint squad will be the stars\\\".\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hoy\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"five golds\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"a more realistic target\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"the women sprint squad\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"the stars\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of Finucane, he said: \\\"Emma will be feeling the pressure to a certain degree, but I would not be surprised if she wins all three.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999907492861403, \"rank\": 9.245628366532346e-06, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Finucane\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain degree\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People might not know her now, but they will know who she is after the Games.\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"People\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She will probably be the superstar of the team, and the reality is she has the potential to do four more Games after this one.\\\"\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the superstar\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"four more Games\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"this one\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The width of the Paris velodrome - wider than most, London included - ought to play to the strengths of the bigger riders, like Finucane's team-mate Sophie Capewell, who also ought to get more of an aerodynamic advantage from the new skinsuits.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999042092941, \"rank\": 9.193844212143694e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"score\": 0.999997246383526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Capewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The width\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1673}, {\"ngram\": \"the strengths\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"the bigger riders\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1785}, {\"ngram\": \"an aerodynamic advantage\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"the new skinsuits\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the third member of GB's women's sprint operation, Katy Marchant, is also in the medal mix.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9783241097042519, \"rank\": 0.022156139944383778, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the third member\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal mix\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's sprint squad lack quite the same strength, such is the dominance of the Dutch, but Kenny is tipping Jack Carlin for keirin gold.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.613853271635085, \"rank\": 0.3738221026781218, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherla